00:05:49.110 --> 00:05:55.910
We brought this up because we wanted
to examine this icon in great detail.

00:05:56.020 --> 00:06:01.700
This icon, which is the preview icon,
it's an icon for an application

00:06:01.700 --> 00:06:08.490
that allows you to view images.

00:06:08.490 --> 00:06:08.490
This really embodies...

00:06:08.860 --> 00:06:12.700
Every aspect an icon in Aqua can achieve.

00:06:12.800 --> 00:06:14.640
It's really what started it all for us.

00:06:14.640 --> 00:06:22.730
It's got 32-bit vivid color,
lines and curves are realized

00:06:22.730 --> 00:06:25.500
through anti-aliasing.

00:06:25.500 --> 00:06:27.420
You can get brilliant curves this way.

00:06:27.420 --> 00:06:32.320
Shadows give a sense of depth
and translucency gives a sense of

00:06:32.320 --> 00:06:37.710
realism to objects like the glass
in the loop in the corner there.

00:06:39.650 --> 00:06:41.920
The photo illustrative
style that we've got,

00:06:42.000 --> 00:06:48.500
as you see, is a combination of stylized
illustration and image.

00:06:49.010 --> 00:06:51.500
The intent is to

00:06:52.070 --> 00:06:56.130
Deliver an object that
is somewhat believable.

00:06:56.130 --> 00:06:59.890
Unlike cartoon type objects
or icons of the past,

00:07:00.010 --> 00:07:05.400
photo-realism or photo-illustrative
as we tend to call it within the team,

00:07:05.560 --> 00:07:08.780
tends to communicate in a different way.

00:07:08.780 --> 00:07:13.010
It sort of lays down the foundation
of something that we call emotive.

00:07:13.400 --> 00:07:19.030
The emotive nature of this icon
can be described as... well,

00:07:19.030 --> 00:07:21.080
I guess if you were to
just look at this thing,

00:07:21.160 --> 00:07:23.790
the pictures are arranged
like they would be on a table.

00:07:23.790 --> 00:07:31.790
They are like they're being used,
like the viewing... the viewing...

00:07:32.280 --> 00:07:36.430
You've been using the loop to look at the
images and it really sets the scene of

00:07:36.440 --> 00:07:38.590
someone who's actually using this thing.

00:07:38.600 --> 00:07:42.200
It communicates the activity
of looking at pictures.

00:07:42.260 --> 00:07:45.380
It's really, really effective.

00:07:48.120 --> 00:07:51.000
It's what makes this icon emotive.

00:07:51.000 --> 00:07:55.420
It's also what makes
this icon not emotive.

00:07:55.590 --> 00:08:01.670
This icon is a really,
really universally understood symbol.

00:08:01.670 --> 00:08:06.820
I'm sure many of you have seen it, well,
the men of you have at least seen it on

00:08:06.820 --> 00:08:12.010
the bathrooms all across your travels.

00:08:13.630 --> 00:08:16.250
This icon is a really,
really basic symbol.

00:08:16.350 --> 00:08:19.000
By no means is it emotive.

00:08:19.470 --> 00:08:23.200
What I mean by that is that in the
context of it being on the bathroom door,

00:08:23.200 --> 00:08:25.850
it communicates men's bathroom.

00:08:25.910 --> 00:08:30.900
You take it out of its context,
it no longer communicates men's bathroom.

00:08:30.930 --> 00:08:33.180
Being flashed here on
the screen right now,

00:08:33.300 --> 00:08:36.500
it's just saying "man."
That's all it's communicating.

00:08:36.560 --> 00:08:40.020
For it to be an Aqua icon,
it would have to be emotive.

00:08:40.070 --> 00:08:45.770
It would have to communicate that it's
a men's bathroom outside of its context,

00:08:45.830 --> 00:08:47.390
no matter where it would be.

00:08:47.450 --> 00:08:50.240
And so if you were to
re-render this thing,

00:08:56.760 --> 00:08:59.700
If you were to re-render this thing,
it might look something like this.

00:08:59.760 --> 00:09:09.860
Which... kind of looks
like me a little bit.

00:09:09.890 --> 00:09:12.200
I think the trajectory
is a little bit off,

00:09:12.200 --> 00:09:12.440
but...

00:09:16.260 --> 00:09:19.810
But the head's close.

00:09:19.950 --> 00:09:22.900
The emotive nature of
this icon is so clear.

00:09:22.920 --> 00:09:29.040
You can totally tell it's a man
and it's someone relieving himself.

00:09:29.160 --> 00:09:32.430
It's the emotive nature of the icon.

00:09:32.460 --> 00:09:34.170
So that's what emotive icons really are.

00:09:34.240 --> 00:09:36.680
They're icons that tell a story.

00:09:36.750 --> 00:09:40.300
They're an extension of the basic,
basic symbol.

00:09:40.310 --> 00:09:44.800
And they're generally
universally understood.

00:09:45.130 --> 00:09:49.550
So, what we've been talking about so far,
the photo illustrative

00:09:49.690 --> 00:09:53.540
quality of our icons,

00:09:53.950 --> 00:09:56.800
Emotive nature of the icons
are all building blocks to

00:09:56.800 --> 00:09:58.900
something that we call genres.

00:09:58.990 --> 00:10:05.900
And genres, like I mentioned earlier on,
are a means to classify applications.

