00:10:33.710 --> 00:10:37.800
The top row is one particular genre
and the second is another one.

00:10:37.800 --> 00:10:43.150
And you can tell this because the ones
in the top are obviously full of color.

00:10:43.300 --> 00:10:46.920
They have a consistent angle to them,
while the ones on the bottom

00:10:46.920 --> 00:10:50.760
are muted and they're generally
straight on from a perspective.

00:10:53.170 --> 00:10:58.990
This sort of thing really makes
sense in the context of the doc,

00:10:59.030 --> 00:11:03.210
where you can find a whole
bunch of applications,

00:11:03.210 --> 00:11:06.500
as many of you have been finding out.

00:11:06.720 --> 00:11:10.070
Here we've got a slide that
has the icons shuffled.

00:11:10.250 --> 00:11:12.890
If we reorder them simply,
you'll see that it's really,

00:11:12.890 --> 00:11:16.000
really clear to pick out two
types of things going on,

00:11:16.110 --> 00:11:18.230
two genres, as we like to call them.

00:11:18.230 --> 00:11:23.050
That's kind of like the dynamics,
the mechanics, rather,

00:11:23.090 --> 00:11:27.040
of how these things work,
how the genres work.

00:11:27.100 --> 00:11:33.100
How we employ them on X is
through something that we call

00:11:33.100 --> 00:11:38.060
the user application and the
utility application genres.

00:11:38.160 --> 00:11:43.010
These are the two genres that
we have defined for Aqua.

00:11:50.020 --> 00:11:54.990
In the user application genre,
we build upon everything that

00:11:54.990 --> 00:11:57.760
we've known about the Mac OS.

00:11:57.760 --> 00:12:03.120
So here is an image of the Mac OS,
original Mac OS application,

00:12:03.120 --> 00:12:06.870
not the original original,
for you purists out there,

00:12:06.880 --> 00:12:12.400
but something that pretty much is close
to the original application diamond.

00:12:12.400 --> 00:12:15.430
And to the left of it
is the new translation,

00:12:15.460 --> 00:12:17.320
the Aqua translation.

00:12:17.810 --> 00:12:23.000
The original Macintosh diamond was
a one-bit symbol that was really,

00:12:23.000 --> 00:12:26.700
really heavy in meaning,
yet light in feeling.

00:12:26.800 --> 00:12:32.560
And when the Mac made the transition
from black and white to color,

00:12:32.560 --> 00:12:35.890
all that was simply done was
the icons were sort of injected

00:12:35.910 --> 00:12:43.490
with color in a really dumb way,
like they would in a coloring book.

00:12:43.770 --> 00:12:50.970
The translation on the right hand
side is paying homage to the diamond.

00:12:51.000 --> 00:12:55.470
You can see a subtle reference,
a similarity to the diamond and the

00:12:55.500 --> 00:12:58.090
tool being the pencil and the pen.

00:12:58.460 --> 00:13:03.460
The translation is now achieved
in more of a photo illustrative,

00:13:03.460 --> 00:13:06.590
emotive, Aqua fashion.

00:13:09.460 --> 00:13:13.240
So, things that define the
user application genre,

00:13:13.240 --> 00:13:17.680
applications that define the user
application genre are apps that

00:13:17.700 --> 00:13:20.990
tend to create or view media.

00:13:21.070 --> 00:13:27.180
And these are apps like TextEdit,
a word processor, or Preview,

00:13:27.180 --> 00:13:29.230
an image viewer.

00:13:29.320 --> 00:13:35.570
And they're frequently used by your
novice user on a day-to-day basis,

00:13:35.570 --> 00:13:37.350
kind of like Mail.

00:13:37.410 --> 00:13:38.900
It's a typical app.

00:13:40.630 --> 00:13:44.280
So these applications are common
in the day to day productivity and

00:13:44.280 --> 00:13:47.700
recreation of most of your users.

00:13:48.100 --> 00:13:54.780
Visually, the genre is defined by
a desk-like perspective.

00:13:54.900 --> 00:13:56.850
We'll talk about that in a second.

00:13:56.930 --> 00:14:01.380
They're designed to be approachable,
friendly, if you will,

00:14:01.440 --> 00:14:04.460
because they are typically
used by your novice user,

00:14:04.460 --> 00:14:07.960
and for that reason they're inviting.

00:14:08.330 --> 00:14:12.430
They're made inviting through
the use of vibrant color,

00:14:12.480 --> 00:14:15.760
