00:22:27.520 --> 00:22:33.490
So up until this point we've been looking
at applications and what it means to

00:22:33.570 --> 00:22:37.930
be emotive and photo illustrative.

00:22:38.200 --> 00:22:42.740
There are other aspects to icons on X.

00:22:42.780 --> 00:22:48.500
Those can be illustrated when we
start looking at the families.

00:22:48.500 --> 00:22:53.840
Families are, again,
they're a way to relate objects

00:22:53.910 --> 00:22:56.590
to the application icon.

00:22:56.610 --> 00:23:01.970
It's actually an old concept,
but we've just sort of carried

00:23:01.970 --> 00:23:01.970
it forward in Mac OS X.

00:23:02.660 --> 00:23:05.880
So here in this illustration you'll
see that the document icons at the

00:23:05.880 --> 00:23:08.560
bottom relate to the preview icon.

00:23:08.810 --> 00:23:10.770
They're branded, if you will.

00:23:11.030 --> 00:23:15.650
They all communicate some
relationship to the preview icon.

00:23:16.380 --> 00:23:19.360
The next image, the iTunes family.

00:23:19.540 --> 00:23:24.740
You'll see that the MusicNote brand
is carried off into every aspect.

00:23:24.800 --> 00:23:28.770
There's a preferences icon at the bottom,
a playlist.

00:23:30.520 --> 00:23:32.600
and a sound document.

00:23:32.740 --> 00:23:34.590
But it all communicates iTunes.

00:23:34.730 --> 00:23:37.180
The relationship is clear.

00:23:38.490 --> 00:23:43.900
So, with the document icon,
like we did with the application icon,

00:23:44.000 --> 00:23:49.300
the application diamond,
we built upon what was already there.

00:23:49.400 --> 00:23:54.820
But this time, gone are the black lines,
gone are the restrictions

00:23:54.840 --> 00:24:00.900
of 45 and 90 degrees,
and in comes the subtleties

00:24:01.010 --> 00:24:04.400
and the dimension of the
dog ear created by shadow.

00:24:05.400 --> 00:24:07.720
So, with the document icon,
like we did with the application icon,

00:24:07.720 --> 00:24:09.960
the application diamond,
we built upon what was already there.

00:24:09.960 --> 00:24:12.240
But this time, gone are the black lines,
gone are the restrictions

00:24:12.240 --> 00:24:14.200
of 45 and 90 degrees,
and in comes the subtleties

00:24:14.200 --> 00:24:16.090
and the dimension of the
dog ear created by shadow.

00:24:19.860 --> 00:24:26.110
So the relationship to the application
and the document is made through using

00:24:26.110 --> 00:24:29.800
the media on the document itself.

00:24:29.800 --> 00:24:35.560
So you'll note the document icon
has the media from the preview,

00:24:35.560 --> 00:24:36.790
but the tool has been removed.

00:24:36.790 --> 00:24:41.800
And that's to communicate a sense
of media that's been created.

00:24:41.800 --> 00:24:45.780
The tool again reinforces
the idea of the application,

00:24:45.860 --> 00:24:46.480
not the media.

00:24:46.480 --> 00:24:49.780
So therefore,
it makes sense to just remove the tool.

00:24:49.800 --> 00:24:51.150
there.

00:24:53.900 --> 00:25:05.300
[Transcript missing]

00:25:05.520 --> 00:25:08.100
We call that labeling.

00:25:08.100 --> 00:25:16.300
The image up here on screen communicates
a preview icon that is a kind of JPEG.

00:25:16.300 --> 00:25:20.280
So the difference that you'll find is,

00:25:20.950 --> 00:25:24.260
This information,
the supplemental information,

00:25:24.260 --> 00:25:26.700
is integrated within the document.

00:25:26.700 --> 00:25:29.900
It's not appended to the
document as a placard.

00:25:29.900 --> 00:25:34.060
It's really just sort of
integrated in a clean manner,

00:25:34.070 --> 00:25:37.790
and it doesn't clutter
up the document at all.

00:25:40.580 --> 00:25:45.980
In the case of the preferences icon,
we've got two elements that

00:25:45.980 --> 00:25:48.170
describe the preference.

00:25:48.610 --> 00:25:54.800
On the right hand side,
