are branded on the right hand side,
while the light switch draws a

00:26:13.860 --> 00:26:18.190
reference to the system preferences
icon on the left hand side.

00:26:19.200 --> 00:26:23.040
So branding is a very,
very important function of

00:26:23.050 --> 00:26:25.150
a lot of the document icons.

00:26:27.420 --> 00:26:33.940
Looking at device icons in 10,
you note that the items on the

00:26:33.940 --> 00:26:37.400
top row are of a pluggable nature.

00:26:37.400 --> 00:26:41.870
These are drives that are external
but are sort of hot pluggable drives,

00:26:41.900 --> 00:26:45.200
things that can come and go,
physical drives, if you will.

00:26:45.200 --> 00:26:50.080
They're branded in a way that they
indicate the bus that they're mounted on.

00:26:50.080 --> 00:26:55.300
So we've got the FireWire drive,
the USB drive, and the SCSI drive.

00:26:56.270 --> 00:27:01.340
And drives below that are drives
that are internal in a sense that

00:27:01.450 --> 00:27:04.120
you can't really see them or it's
not that important to see them.

00:27:07.010 --> 00:27:13.100
We've got with the blue globe iDisk,
next to it is the internal hard disk.

00:27:14.600 --> 00:27:21.400
[Transcript missing]

00:27:22.260 --> 00:27:24.330
A note about the internal hard disk.

00:27:24.350 --> 00:27:31.090
Because what we're trying to do is
communicate physicality to these objects,

00:27:31.410 --> 00:27:35.300
It really communicates
the internal hard disk.

00:27:35.300 --> 00:27:38.300
It really gives you a sense of
what it looks like from the inside.

00:27:38.300 --> 00:27:42.400
Although people may never see it,
it's probably a good idea to let

00:27:42.400 --> 00:27:44.610
them know what it really looks like.

00:27:45.530 --> 00:27:48.570
With devices,
it's about the physical nature,

00:27:48.580 --> 00:27:52.630
it is what it is,
versus what it should be or how it

00:27:52.630 --> 00:27:55.700
feels with the application icons.

00:27:57.660 --> 00:28:02.240
Looking at removable media,
the focus shifts from the

00:28:02.240 --> 00:28:04.750
device to the media itself.

00:28:04.750 --> 00:28:09.490
So you don't represent the
zip drive or the CD-ROM drive.

00:28:09.550 --> 00:28:15.000
It's really more of an intimate
relationship about the media itself.

00:28:15.060 --> 00:28:20.210
And here we've got a selection
of different types of media.

00:28:20.470 --> 00:28:30.240
Floppy disks, Zip disk, Jazz disk, DVD,
