You'll note though that the perspective
is different from that of the

00:28:37.900 --> 00:28:43.490
"So hard, pluggable, or internal devices
in that it's straight.

00:28:43.870 --> 00:28:48.460
And that's because that's what your
relationship is with that type of media.

00:28:48.570 --> 00:28:53.710
You normally hold ZIP cartridges
in your hand and CDs in your hand.

00:28:58.990 --> 00:29:04.350
So, looking at toolbars,
this is an illustration

00:29:04.350 --> 00:29:06.700
of the Finder toolbar.

00:29:07.480 --> 00:29:11.690
Something that's important to note
is that unlike the other icons that

00:29:11.690 --> 00:29:16.420
we've been talking about this far,
especially the user applications,

00:29:16.460 --> 00:29:21.170
which are layered objects upon objects,
items in the toolbar are

00:29:21.170 --> 00:29:23.640
designed to be singular objects.

00:29:23.690 --> 00:29:28.770
So they communicate the
action with one icon,

00:29:28.890 --> 00:29:30.560
one object.

00:29:31.410 --> 00:29:34.670
I'll get to the
contradiction in a minute.

00:29:34.710 --> 00:29:39.910
The computer communicates what it is.

00:29:40.080 --> 00:29:42.620
The home is a single object.

00:29:42.640 --> 00:29:45.990
The heart is a single
object for favorites.

00:29:46.270 --> 00:29:51.310
And the three objects that represent
applications are fashioned in a way

00:29:51.340 --> 00:29:53.900
to really communicate a single object.

00:29:54.000 --> 00:29:56.040
So they really form an A.

00:29:56.040 --> 00:30:01.930
So it's read first as a single object,
then in closer detail, close examination,

00:30:01.930 --> 00:30:04.400
you'll see that it's made up of three.

00:30:04.500 --> 00:30:08.200
And also,
there's a singular color usage for

00:30:08.200 --> 00:30:11.800
all these objects on the toolbar.

00:30:11.830 --> 00:30:15.940
The computer is predominantly dark blue.

00:30:16.200 --> 00:30:25.800
[Transcript missing]

00:30:30.500 --> 00:30:36.190
The perspective for items on the
toolbar are similar to that of items

00:30:36.270 --> 00:30:38.150
in the utility application genre.

00:30:38.170 --> 00:30:40.930
They are dead on.

00:31:00.710 --> 00:31:00.710
And that can be illustrated in
another crude drawing like this.

00:31:00.710 --> 00:31:00.710
You'll see, again,
if we were to look through the

00:31:00.710 --> 00:31:00.710
camera like we have been at the
bottom and look in the top left,

00:31:00.710 --> 00:31:00.710
you would see something like
the home in that perspective.

00:31:00.710 --> 00:31:00.710
And then on the top right,
what it would look like if it was

00:31:00.710 --> 00:31:00.710
rendered out in that perspective.

00:31:03.570 --> 00:31:09.540
There's quite a bit of function
that comes to designing a toolbar.

00:31:09.580 --> 00:31:16.160
The singular item icon,
the attention to form,

00:31:16.160 --> 00:31:24.850
and the singular color usage all plays
a great sort of functional purpose in

00:31:24.970 --> 00:31:29.650
that it really makes it easy to pick out
objects on the toolbar at a quick scan.

00:31:29.660 --> 00:31:34.170
In this illustration,
you'll note that objects can be

00:31:34.170 --> 00:31:38.890
broken down into really easily
understandable primitives.

00:31:38.890 --> 00:31:41.650
In the computer, we've just got a square.

00:31:41.650 --> 00:31:45.060
In the home, there's a triangle that
sits on top of a square.

00:31:45.060 --> 00:31:48.550
In favorites,
there's just a simple heart,

00:31:48.550 --> 00:31:52.460
and the apps can be
communicated as a triangle.

00:31:52.460 --> 00:31:55.780
It really makes it easy to
quickly scan through and pick

00:31:55.780 --> 00:31:57.990
something out based on its shape.

00:31:58.060 --> 00:31:59.600
And then that's reinforcement.

00:31:59.690 --> 00:32:01.960
It's reinforced by the
other elements as well.

00:32:01.960 --> 00:32:06.980
So, in practice,

00:32:08.800 --> 00:32:14.800
[Transcript missing]

00:32:14.920 --> 00:32:19.430
Elements on the toolbar within an
application should be consistent

00:32:19.570 --> 00:32:22.360
and use common elements.

00:32:22.360 --> 00:32:29.890
We say that because using consistent
elements through color or repurposing

00:32:29.890 --> 00:32:35.540
elements allows for each application
to develop a sense of character.

00:32:35.540 --> 00:32:39.510
In this case,
you'll see that the Mail toolbar

00:32:39.510 --> 00:32:45.130
reinforces the language that was
started or originated by the application

00:32:45.140 --> 00:32:52.160
icon by using stamps and the color of
blue is carried all across the toolbar.

00:32:52.160 --> 00:32:55.820
Objects on the right hand side
are a little bit different because

00:32:55.820 --> 00:32:59.730
they have different functions,
yet they still relate

00:32:59.730 --> 00:33:02.040
visually in terms of color.

00:33:02.040 --> 00:33:07.080
And a little stamp
element in the corner as

00:33:08.980 --> 00:33:14.690
Materials are a really
new concept for Mac OS X.

00:33:14.730 --> 00:33:17.920
We've never looked at materials.

00:33:18.600 --> 00:33:23.770
What I mean by that is that
we've never really looked at

00:33:23.770 --> 00:33:30.980
what it means to communicate,
say, the plasticity of the CD in iTunes

00:33:30.980 --> 00:33:34.540
or any of the other details.

00:33:34.540 --> 00:33:39.530
We study a lot of real world objects
when we go off and we render our objects.

00:33:39.610 --> 00:33:43.940
And that's to fully
communicate the realism,

00:33:43.940 --> 00:33:43.940
to

00:33:44.230 --> 00:33:49.440
Reinforce the photo-illustrative
nature and to really

00:33:55.240 --> 00:33:56.360
So there's really no question when you
come across these things what it is.

00:33:56.760 --> 00:34:03.470
If we were to look at some of them,
the middle icon is an icon for Sketch.

00:34:03.550 --> 00:34:06.690
You can see it has pieces of tape,
Scotch tape.

00:34:06.730 --> 00:34:14.290
You can almost see the 3M logo in there.

00:34:14.290 --> 00:34:14.290
The stickies

00:34:14.570 --> 00:34:19.410
It really has a sense of the sticky
type of paper where there's glue on

00:34:19.410 --> 00:34:24.250
the back and the way it's frayed up
on the top because it's only glued

00:34:24.250 --> 00:34:26.670
on the top portion of the paper.

00:34:26.670 --> 00:34:32.130
The glass loop in preview and the metal
brim around the Sherlock magnifying

00:34:32.130 --> 00:34:35.140
glass really gives it a sense of weight.

00:34:35.140 --> 00:34:39.010
You'll know how that
feels when you pick it up.

00:34:39.640 --> 00:34:46.700
And the battery monitor,
which we call the AquaCell inside.

00:34:47.270 --> 00:34:50.600
really communicates a sense of glass.

00:34:50.600 --> 00:34:59.970
A note about transparency-- we tend to
use transparency in a meaningful way.

00:35:00.070 --> 00:35:03.720
The only time we sort of
break away from that is in the

00:35:03.720 --> 00:35:05.680
case of the battery monitor.

00:35:05.770 --> 00:35:09.150
And that's because it
